OL,6,FOn Saturday, Scottish airline Loganair
OL,7,Fannounced that it would take over many
OL,8,Fof the routes between the Channel
OL,9,FIslands and the UK, which were
OL,10,Fformerly operated by Blue Islands,
OL,11,Fwith Aurigny also scheduling an
OL,12,Fadditional interim of flights from
OL,13,FGuernsey.
OL,15,FMark Helyar, President of Guernsey
OL,16,FStates Trading Supervisory Board, told
OL,17,FITV News that some of Blue Islands'
OL,18,Fformer workers could potentially find
OL,19,Fnew work under these airlines.
